Trash, trash and more trash
Mar 2016 ‚Ä¢ Family
Over spring break, we went on a 3-day, 2-night cruise of Halong Bay. The images from the online sites and descriptions ("H·∫° Long Bay, in northeast Vietnam, is known for its emerald waters") give you the impression that the area is a pristine natural wonderland. Unfortunately there is too SO MUCH GARBAGE in every direction, so this is a false perception. Part of our itinerary included time for snorkeling and swimming, but there was NO WAY I was going in those waters. It was polluted with everything from used sanitary napkins, to plastic containers, to light bulbs, shoes, clothing, and dozens of plastic bags. I was told that the gov. has begun hiring people to clean-up. During our time on the water, we saw one man in a small boat with a small net collecting some rubbish, but it is going to take a much bigger effort. The area has so much potential, but the trash ruins the whole experience. With the money they are making on the tourism from the Halong Bay cruises, surely there is money to be put into a massive clean-up effort.
